https://github.com/raushan8586/Deploy-NodeApp-to-AWS-EKS-using-Jenkins-Pipeline

Create ubuntu instance
1. Install java and jenkins
2. Install docker in ubuntu EC2 instance

  sudo usermod -aG docker $USER
  sudo chmod 666 /var/run/docker.sock

3. Install eksctl, kubectl, aws cli --> aws configure as jenkins user (sudo -su jenkins) as well along with root user 

4. create EKS cluster

login to jenkins and install nodejs plugin. Go to tools and install nodejs (provide node name --> matching with jenkinsfile)
Got to credentials and configure credentials for gitHub and Docker Hub

5. Create jenkins pipeline using jenkinsfile in the script --> use pipeline script

6. verify
